<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4010] Q.fcall messing up with *this* pointer inside called function</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4010</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Example: I define a basic service&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;br/&gt;
namespace js Auth&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;service AuthSrv {&lt;br/&gt;
    string signin(&lt;br/&gt;
        1:string email,&lt;br/&gt;
        2:string password&lt;br/&gt;
    )&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And set up a Auth es6 class that gonna handle the requests like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;br/&gt;
module.exports = class AuthSrv {&lt;br/&gt;
    constructor() &lt;/p&gt;
{
        this.db = .........
    }

&lt;p&gt;    async signin(email, password) {&lt;br/&gt;
        try &lt;/p&gt;
{
            let user = await this.db.findOne(....)
        }

&lt;p&gt;        ....&lt;br/&gt;
    }&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and instantiate a thrift server like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;br/&gt;
let server = thrift.createServer(AuthProcessor, new AuthSrv());&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this scenario, i&apos;m getting that &lt;b&gt;this&lt;/b&gt; pointer is *&lt;b&gt;undefined&lt;/b&gt;* when signin function is called. Looking at thrift generated code for the processor i saw this line:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;br/&gt;
if (this._handler.signin.length === 2) {&lt;br/&gt;
    Q.fcall(this._handler.signin, args.email, args.password)&lt;br/&gt;
    .then(.....)&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If i change the fcall to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;br/&gt;
if (this._handler.signin.length === 2) {&lt;br/&gt;
    Q.fcall(this._handler.signin.bind(this._handler), args.email, args.password)&lt;br/&gt;
    .then(.....)&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;everything works like a charm and &lt;b&gt;this&lt;/b&gt; pointer is correctly assinged inside signin function call.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
